04548nam a22006615i 9780520950443DE-B159720200424112023.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||200424t20112011cau    fo  d z      eng d  a97805209504437 a10.1525/97805209504432doi  a(DE-B1597)520857  a(OCoLC)747428061  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  acaucUS-CA 4aBX4817 -- .K53 2011eb 7aREL0700002bisacsh04a234.1311 aKlassen, Pamela E., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aSpirits of Protestantism :bMedicine, Healing, and Liberal Christianity /cPamela E. Klassen. 1aBerkeley, CA : bUniversity of California Press, c[2011] 4cÂ©2011  a1 online resource (348 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aThe Anthropology of Christianity ;v1300tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tIllustrations -- tPreface: Pathologies of Modernity -- tAcknowledgments -- tIntroduction: Healing Christians -- tChapter 1. Anthropologies of the Spiritual Body -- tChapter 2. The Gospel of Health and the Scientific Spirit -- tChapter 3. Protestant Experimentalists and the Energy of Love -- tChapter 4. Evil Spirits and the Queer Psyche in an Age of Anxiety -- tChapter 5. Ritual Proximity and the Healing of History -- tConclusion. Critical Condition -- tNotes -- tArchives Consulted -- tSelected Bibliography -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aSpirits of Protestantism reveals how liberal Protestants went from being early-twentieth-century medical missionaries seeking to convert others through science and scripture, to becoming vocal critics of missionary arrogance who experimented with non-western healing modes such as Yoga and Reiki. Drawing on archival and ethnographic sources, Pamela E. Klassen shows how and why the very notion of healing within North America has been infused with a Protestant "supernatural liberalism." In the course of coming to their changing vision of healing, liberal Protestants became pioneers three times over: in the struggle against the cultural and medical pathologizing of homosexuality; in the critique of Christian missionary triumphalism; and in the diffusion of an ever-more ubiquitous anthropology of "body, mind, and spirit." At a time when the political and anthropological significance of Christianity is being hotly debated, Spirits of Protestantism forcefully argues for a reconsideration of the historical legacies and cultural effects of liberal Protestantism, even for the anthropology of religion itself.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aHealing -- Religious aspects -- Protestant churches. 0aHealingxReligious aspectsxProtestant churches. 0aLiberalism (Religion) - North America - History. 0aLiberalism (Religion) -- North America -- History. 0aLiberalism (Religion)xHistoryxNorth America. 0aLiberalism (Religion)zNorth AmericaxHistory. 0aProtestant churches -- North America -- History. 0aProtestant churchesxHistoryxNorth America. 0aProtestant churcheszNorth AmericaxHistory. 0aProtestantism -- North America -- History. 0aProtestantismxHistoryxNorth America. 0aProtestantismzNorth AmericaxHistory. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520950443423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520950443.jpg  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles